[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dumfries attacker punched victim 'a number of times'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 23-year-old man was punched in the head "a number of times" in an attack on a Dumfries street.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
His assailant approached him from behind on Brodie Avenue at about 21:30 on Sunday and carried out the assault.
The attacker is described as between 40 and 50 years old, of thin build with short grey hair.
He was wearing blue jeans, a dark coloured top and trainers and was in the company of a woman, described as being short and aged about 19.
The victim suffered minor injuries but did not require medical assistance.
